  "body": "Since JSX code is now advocated as needing a .jsx extension, it would make sense to do a major version release that breaks backward compat by switching to \"always assume code is in .jsx, unless otherwise specified using the -x flag\".\n\nThe major semver bump would ensure existing projects are not affected by that realignment with current advocacy and practice.\n",
